---
// /services/consultancy/monitoring-evaluation.astro
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const pageTitle = "MEARL Consultancy Services | ActionPath Africa";
const pageDescription = "Practical, affordable MEARL systems designed specifically for local organizations in the African context. We partner with organizations to build or strengthen their Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability, Research, and Learning systems.";
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <main>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="cluster-hero">
      <div class="cluster-hero-inner">
        <div class="cluster-breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i>
          <a href="/services/consultancy">Consultancy</a> <i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i>
          <span>MEARL</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cluster-icon-large">
          <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
        </div>
        <h1 class="all-red">Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability, Research & Learning</h1>
        <p class="cluster-subhead">Organizations often struggle with M&E because donors demand evidence of impact, yet many local organizations lack the internal capacity to track it properly. Donors want proof that resources invested have translated into tangible, positive change. Yet, for many local NGOs, CBOs, and social enterprises, building and sustaining a robust MEARL system remains a significant challenge. Limited budgets, technical capacity gaps, and the pressure of day-to-day implementation often leave MEARL as an afterthought rather than a strategic tool.</p>
        <div class="cluster-ctas">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary"><i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> Inquire About MEARL Support</a>
          <a href="/services/consultancy" class="btn-outline"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> All Consultancy Services</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Gap Section -->
    <section class="cluster-gap">
      <div class="cluster-container">
        <div class="gap-content">
          <div class="section-header">
            <div class="section-eyebrow"><i class="fas fa-eye"></i> What We've Witnessed</div>
            <h2>Addressing the <span class="accent-red">MEARL Gap</span></h2>
            <div class="section-divider"></div>
          </div>
          <p>At ActionPath Africa, we have witnessed this gap firsthand through our years of training in project management, organizational documentation, and results-based planning. We have seen brilliant community-led initiatives struggle to articulate their impact, fail to meet donor reporting requirements, or repeat the same mistakes because no system existed to capture learning. In response, we have developed a comprehensive MEARL consultancy service designed specifically for local organizations. Our approach is not theoretical. It is practical, affordable, and deeply rooted in the realities of the African context—rural accessibility, low-literacy populations, limited internet connectivity, and resource constraints.</p>
          <p>We partner with organizations to build or strengthen their MEARL systems across five interconnected pillars: Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability, Research, and Learning.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Five Pillars Section -->
    <section class="cluster-pillars">
      <div class="cluster-container">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-eyebrow"><i class="fas fa-cubes"></i> Our Framework</div>
          <h2>Five Interconnected <span class="accent-red">Pillars</span></h2>
          <div class="section-divider"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="pillars-grid">
          <div class="pillar-card">
            <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="fas fa-chart-simple"></i></div>
            <h3>Monitoring</h3>
            <p>Tracking progress in real-time to make adjustments along the way.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-card">
            <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="fas fa-clipboard-list"></i></div>
            <h3>Evaluation</h3>
            <p>Assessing whether your interventions actually achieved what they set out to do.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-card">
            <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="fas fa-handshake"></i></div>
            <h3>Accountability</h3>
            <p>Ensuring your organization answers to the people it serves and the donors who fund it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-card">
            <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="fas fa-microscope"></i></div>
            <h3>Research</h3>
            <p>Generating deeper insights into the problems you are trying to solve.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar-card">
            <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="fas fa-book-open"></i></div>
            <h3>Learning</h3>
            <p>Closing the loop by using evidence to improve future programs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Our Approach Section -->
    <section class="cluster-approach">
      <div class="cluster-container">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="section-eyebrow"><i class="fas fa-gem"></i> Our Approach</div>
          <h2>How We <span class="accent-red">Work</span></h2>
          <div class="section-divider"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="approach-grid">
          <div class="approach-item">
            <i class="fas fa-users"></i>
            <div>
              <h3>Participation</h3>
              <p>We do not design systems for organizations; we design systems with them. The organization's staff, beneficiaries, and stakeholders are involved at every stage.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="approach-item">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
            <div>
              <h3>Simplicity</h3>
              <p>We avoid academic complexity and jargon. If a farmer or a community volunteer cannot understand it, we redesign it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="approach-item">
            <i class="fas fa-bullseye"></i>
            <div>
              <h3>Utility</h3>
              <p>Every indicator we track, every survey question we ask, and every report we write must have a clear purpose. If the data will not be used to make a decision, we do not collect it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="approach-item">
            <i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i>
            <div>
              <h3>Capacity Strengthening</h3>
              <p>We prioritize training, mentorship, and knowledge transfer over doing the work for them, and use global MEARL standards but adapt them to local realities — low literacy, multiple languages, limited electricity, and cultural norms around communication and authority.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="approach-item">
            <i class="fas fa-shield-heart"></i>
            <div>
              <h3>Ethics & Do-No-Harm</h3>
              <p>We prioritize the safety and dignity of beneficiaries above data collection. Informed consent, confidentiality, and safeguarding are non-negotiable.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="approach-cta">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary"><i class="fas fa-calendar-alt"></i> Request a MEARL Consultation</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Services -->
    <section class="cluster-related">
      <div class="cluster-container">
        <div class="related-grid">
          <div class="related-card">
            <i class="fas fa-book-open"></i>
            <h3>Curriculum Development</h3>
            <p>Develop monitoring-friendly training curricula.</p>
            <a href="/services/consultancy/curriculum-development">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="related-card">
            <i class="fas fa-heart"></i>
            <h3>Counseling Services</h3>
            <p>MEARL for psychosocial and protection programs.</p>
            <a href="/services/consultancy/psychosocial-support">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="related-card">
            <i class="fas fa-tasks"></i>
            <h3>Project Planning & Management</h3>
            <p>Build MEARL into your project plans.</p>
            <a href="/services/training/project-management">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="related-card">
            <i class="fas fa-hand-holding-heart"></i>
            <h3>How to Establish a CBO</h3>
            <p>Build accountability into your CBO systems.</p>
            <a href="/services/training/establish-cbo">Learn more →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  .cluster-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e293b 0%, #0f172a 100%);
    padding: 4rem 0;
    color: white;
  }
  .cluster-hero-inner {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }
  .cluster-breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .cluster-breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--green-lt);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .cluster-breadcrumb i {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    margin: 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .cluster-icon-large {
    font-size: 4rem;
    color: var(--green);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .cluster-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.6rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .all-red {
    color: var(--red);
  }
  .accent-red { color: var(--red); }
  .cluster-subhead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .cluster-ctas {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .btn-primary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--red), var(--red-dark));
    color: white;
    padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 50px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 25px rgba(192, 57, 43, 0.4);
  }
  .btn-outline {
    border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
    background: transparent;
    color: white;
    padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 50px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  .btn-outline:hover {
    border-color: var(--green);
    background: rgba(39,238,49,0.1);
  }
  .cluster-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }
  .section-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .section-eyebrow {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    background: var(--red-soft);
    color: var(--red);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.4rem 1.3rem;
    border-radius: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }
  .section-divider {
    width: 70px;
    height: 4px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--red), var(--green));
    margin: 1rem auto 0;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .cluster-gap {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: white;
  }
  .gap-content p {
    color: var(--gray-md);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .cluster-pillars {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: var(--gray-sf);
  }
  .pillars-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .pillar-card {
    background: white;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .pillar-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-5px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    border-color: var(--red);
  }
  .pillar-icon {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--green);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .pillar-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }
  .pillar-card p {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--gray-md);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .cluster-approach {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    background: white;
  }
  .approach-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .approach-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    background: var(--gray-sf);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 16px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  .approach-item:hover {
    transform: translateX(5px);
  }
  .approach-item i {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    color: var(--red);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .approach-item h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }
  .approach-item p {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--gray-md);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .approach-cta {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .cluster-related {
    padding: 3rem 0 5rem;
    background: var(--gray-sf);
  }
  .related-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .related-card {
    background: white;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    text-align: center;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  .related-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-5px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }
  .related-card i {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    color: var(--green);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .related-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }
  .related-card p {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--gray-md);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .related-card a {
    color: var(--red);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }
  .related-card a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .pillars-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
    .related-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pillars-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .approach-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .related-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cluster-hero h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
    .section-header h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .approach-item { flex-direction: column; text-align: center; }
  }
</style>